reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 16, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great gps with features we love
reviews.reviewText: I got this for my son for his birthday. Today as he doesn't have one. It seems to be a really good model and he will get many yrs of use from it . We have tried other brands but always come back to garmin as we like the set up the best. It's very easy to use and update and the voices are not as annoying as some out there. The speed limit, miles to or time to destination is a nice feature , and the new gas station /food signs are a nice addition. Also the school zone warning is one of my fave things when you're in an area you are not familiar with. By far our favorite GPS systems.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perhaps I will be as fortunate with this model
reviews.reviewText: I have used for about 1 year and it works well. Some of the features are not as common sense for us that are electronically challenged. Appears to be very accurate and maps, for the most part are up to date. My last Garmin lasted for 5 yrs before it went loopy. Perhaps I will be as fortunate with this model!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 29, 2016
reviews.reviewText: Terrific GPS unit. I had an older, smaller Garmin but this one is the best! Easy & clear operation & directions. Excellent routes and smaller, newer streets identified. Excellent price, too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2015
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars For the price, excellent
reviews.reviewText: Coming off of a very old Garmin GPS, I was very pleased with this model. It's much faster than my old model and responds quickly to searches. I also like the split screen mode and the "miles to" feature that shows gas and bathrooms. Sometimes, though, it didn't know the difference between a rest stop with bathrooms and one without. On long drives this is crucial info. Also, once it didn't recognize a road while driving in Canda. It didn't turn out to be a big deal, but I would have thought it would come preloaded with the latest maps.
